pullRequest.body: This moves some content out of `Init`, deprecates some material that was ported from Lean 3 but is used nowhere, and removes some attributes and instances which are duplicated from Lean or Batteries.

bors d+
Thanks!

I looked over everything. Thanks a lot for doing this clean-up.
I trust you that all attributes you're removing are in fact present in batteries or core.
Apart from that, I only have a few minor comments.

bors d+
Thanks!
Should this say what to use instead?
It's just `rfl`, and it seems no one uses it, and it dates from before the port. 🤷‍♀️
Also in this file
We don't seem to have anywhere `Nat.succ_zero : succ 0 = 1`. This is probably because it is not needed anywhere, apparently!

```suggestion
-- The remaining theorems in this section were ported from Lean 3,
Looks like this one was forgotten.
Nice clean-up.
This also was phrased for Sort*, can you re-add this (or say why this is not desirable), please?
Good catch! Done.
Just flagging this for other reviewers: you are deleting this instance. Do we have a test this works?
Yes, it is used in a few places, e.g. Mathlib.Topology.Order.LeftRightNhds and Archive.Imo.Imo1964Q1
What happened to this instance?
This was a duplicate of `PSigma.instWellFoundedRelation` in `lean4`.
:+1: ... and the `lean4` instance even applies to Sort. Thanks for explaining!
I presume this is also just unused: can you add a comment as in the other file?
Same here.
